{
  "texts": [
    "Users are not required to have access to specialized hardware or software, nor a deep understanding of machine learning or natural language processing.",
    "Instead, LLMs are accessible through application programming interfaces (APIs) and are capable of handling complex tasks with minimal (few-shot) or no (zero-shot) prior information.",
    "This accessibility offers a more intuitive and natural way of interacting with computers (de Wynter et al., 2023).",
    "LLMs, with their foundation in neural network architectures, are adept at handling a wide range of interactions.",
    "They can engage in dialogue, rectify mistakes, counteract incorrect presuppositions, and decline unsuitable inquiries, all within a conversational framework."
  ]
}